### [4 Kings (2 Kings) Chapter 20](../../../bib/kjv/kg2020.htm#001.md)

[4 Kings (2 Kings)](../../../bib/kjv/kg2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">kg2 20:0</span></span>

Overview

[Kg2 20:1](../../../bib/kjv/kg2020.htm#001.md), Hezekiah, having received a
message of death, by prayer has his life lengthened; [Kg2
20:8](../../../bib/kjv/kg2020.htm#008.md), The sun goes ten degrees
backward for a sign of that promise; [Kg2
20:12](../../../bib/kjv/kg2020.htm#012.md), Berodach-baladan sending to
visit Hezekiah, because of the wonder, has notice of his treasures; [Kg2
20:14](../../../bib/kjv/kg2020.htm#014.md), Isaiah understanding thereof,
foretells the Babylonian captivity; [Kg2
20:20](../../../bib/kjv/kg2020.htm#020.md), Manasseh succeeds Hezekiah.

